                      "content": "Uncle Bob",
                      "id": ""
                    }
                  ],
                  "content": "https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2017/10/04/CodeIsNotTheAnswer.html",
                  "id": ""
                }
              ],
              "content": "",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "Most of the time architecture is the ",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "italic",
              "childNodes": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "childNodes": [],
                  "content": "wrong thing",
                  "id": ""
                }
              ],
              "content": "",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": " to be working on since it's hard to        quantify a business value. \"If it ain't broke don't fix it.\" On larger projects there can be a lot of fear and        uncertainty around changing code critical to the build system or core architecture. Changing that code is risky        and often requires a blind 'break and fix' approach that you can only test        so much on a local or lower environment.",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "But, ",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "a",
              "childNodes": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "childNodes": [],
                  "content": "tragedy of the commons",
                  "id": ""
                }
              ],
              "content": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tragedy_of_the_commons",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": " is a thing in        software development especially with autonomous product-focused delivery teams. Eventually, it all slows down and impacts the        business. So what do you do        about it?",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "Take responsibility.  I guess that's the point of side-projects. Make as many mistakes in the toy system as you can. Fix them.        Write about it. Level up.",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "h2",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "How?",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "        I'm going to 'start from scratch' with this project so that I get a complete understanding of each step; adding        new libraries/frameworks/tools/abstractions incrementally when a 'real' need occurs like: I can't write the code        I        need, the        system can't handle load, I run out of space, etc.      ",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "I'm a believer in ",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "let it become a problem",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": " as opposed to ",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "code",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "solve it upfront",
              "id": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": ". Draft up        some guiding principles, work under those constraints until you can't.",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "Don't solve for that edge case. Don't support that feature. Don't nest that object. Don't make a list of one        item. Don't use that framework. Don't make a service. Don't create a DSL. Don't make the API 'more        flexible'.",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "Don't deliver a box of Ikea parts and tell me you shipped a dresser.",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "childNodes": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "childNodes": [],
              "content": "Ok, you get the picture â›ª",
              "id": ""
            }
          ],
          "content": "",
          "id": ""
        },
